// =============================================================================
// core/database/sqlite/native/exec/mod.vr
// =============================================================================
// Layer: 7 (façade — sqlite3_exec convenience)
// Spec: SQLite C API — sqlite3_exec(db, sql, cb, pArg, pErrmsg).
//
// The convenience loop:
//   1. Parse SQL into statement segments using the `complete` scanner.
//   2. For each segment: prepare → step until DONE/ROW → invoke cb per row.
//   3. Stop on first error or when cb returns non-zero.
//
// Submodules:
//   * `row`       — column-value list handed to the user callback
//   * `callback`  — CallbackDecision sum
//   * `engine`    — pure driver (caller supplies prepare / step hooks)
// =============================================================================

module core.database.sqlite.native.exec;

public module row;
public module callback;
public module engine;
